{
  "texts": [
    "The surfaceΣ C is the 1/3-fattening of C ⊂ R 2.",
    "That is, Σ C:= {v ∈ R 2: dist(v, C) ≤ 1/3} where dist(v, C) = inf w∈C ∥w -v∥ ∞ and we regard C as a closed subset of the plane.",
    "The marked boundary points are the points of intersection of ∂Σ C with edges of Z 2.",
    "Such a marked boundary point has positive sign if the corresponding edge e ∈ E (which is oriented towards the top left) points out of the surface Σ C, and it has negative sign if the corresponding edge e ∈ E points into the surface.",
    "Finally, each connected boundary component N ∈ Bd(Σ C) is the union of some horizontal and vertical line segments."
  ]
}